featured_reviews.review_id:
Mashaallah beautiful masjid
Spread of islam

Islam is not a national culture and is not a religion bound within the periphery of the national border, but is spread throughout the world as a universal power. Since the origins of Islam in 610 AD, followers of the religion of Islam have been steadily increasing.

In the seventh century Islam emerged as a small community in Mecca and Medina. Prophet Mohammad along with his two followers laid the foundation of this religion. Within a few years of its emergence, all Arabic castes united under the banner of Islam. Within the first two centuries of its development, the influence of Islam spread globally.

Islam, through its continued conquest, took the entire Middle East, North Africa, the Arabian Peninsula, the Iranian region, Central Asia, and the Indus Valley under its sphere of influence. This conquest process continued uninterrupted and later Islam inherited the civilizations of ancient Egypt and Mesopotamia.

Islam does not differentiate between spiritual and temporal, supernatural and practical, religious and secular. Islam accepts wide diversity in state and rule, power, governance and loyalty. It is based on the principle of unity
